The paper proposes a machine learning model for predicting drug-drug interactions, which involves learning a representation of interactions between drug pairs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves designing a novel loss function and using autoencoders, which are common techniques in Computational Engineering (cs.CE) and Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the proposed model on real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
